HEADWORD: Relational
<hw>Re*la"tion*al</hw> <pr>(r?-l?"sh?n-<it>a</it>l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Having relation or kindred; related.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We might be tempted to take these two nations for <qex>relational
stems</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Tooke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Indicating or specifying some relation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Relational</qex> words, as prepositions, auxiliaries,
etc.</q> <rj><qau>R. Morris.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Relationist</ent>⟦br⟧
